<LegalLayout
  title="Privacy Policy"
  description="Sound Buddy is local-first. Your audio never leaves your machine. No telemetry from the app, no accounts, no cross-site tracking. Here's exactly what we do and don't collect."
  updated="July 20, 2026"
>
  <p>
    Sound Buddy is built local-first, and privacy is the whole point. This policy explains — in plain
    English — exactly what stays on your Mac and the little that leaves it.
  </p>

  <div class="callout">
    <p><strong>No audio data leaves your machine.</strong> Sound Buddy analyzes your recordings
    entirely on your Mac. We never upload, collect, or transmit your audio, and it never touches our
    servers — because we don't run any.</p>
  </div>

  <h2>What stays on your Mac</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Your audio.</strong> Recordings, stems, and everything you analyze are processed
      on-device and stored only where you save them.</li>
    <li><strong>Your report cards and analysis.</strong> Grades, metrics, and session data live in
      local files on your machine.</li>
    <li><strong>Your license key.</strong> Stored locally on your device to unlock Pro features.
      It isn't shared or synced anywhere by the app.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>AI is optional — and yours</h2>
  <p>
    If you turn on the AI analyst, you choose the provider: a local model through Ollama, or your own
    API key for a provider you control. Either way, Sound Buddy does not store your AI prompts or the
    responses, and it never proxies AI requests through us. Whatever you send goes directly to the
    provider you picked, under that provider's own terms.
  </p>

  <h2>No telemetry, no analytics, no accounts</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>We don't collect usage analytics or telemetry from the app.</li>
    <li>There are no accounts to create and no profiles to track you across the web.</li>
    <li>This website uses Cloudflare Web Analytics, which is cookieless: it sets no cookies,
      stores no device identifiers, and cannot follow you to other sites. It records aggregate
      page views and referrers only. The Sound Buddy app itself still sends nothing.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Payments and your email</h2>
  <p>
    When you buy Sound Buddy Pro, payment is handled by <a href="https://stripe.com" rel="noopener">Stripe</a>,
    a PCI-compliant payment processor. We never see or store your full card details — Stripe does. The
    email address you check out with is used to deliver your license key and to send purchase and
    support messages related to your subscription. It is not sold, and it is not used for unrelated
    marketing. Stripe's handling of your payment data is covered by <a
      href="https://stripe.com/privacy" rel="noopener">Stripe's privacy policy</a>.
  </p>

  <h2>Support email</h2>
  <p>
    If you email us for support or a refund, we keep that correspondence so we can help you. That's it.
  </p>

  <h2>Children</h2>
  <p>
    Sound Buddy is a professional audio tool intended for adults and isn't directed at children under 13.
  </p>

  <h2>Changes to this policy</h2>
  <p>
    If we ever change what we collect, we'll update this page and the "last updated" date above. Because
    Sound Buddy is local-first by design, our goal is for this policy to stay short.
  </p>
</LegalLayout>
